                            <comment id="16026607" author="steve_rowe" created="Fri, 26 May 2017 18:04:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;On the Language Analysis page:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Removes the CJK section, along with the no-longer-present CJKTokenizer.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Renames the Chinese section to Traditional Chinese (there is already a Simplified Chinese section).&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Adds coverage of &lt;tt&gt;CJKBigramFilter&lt;/tt&gt;, linked to the Traditional Chinese section when used with &lt;tt&gt;StandardTokenizer&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Mentions the possibility of using the default &lt;tt&gt;ICUTokenizer&lt;/tt&gt; configuration with both Traditional and Simplified Chinese.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Adds internal links from the Japanese section to the individual component sections.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Adds a test for Traditional Chinese to Lucene&apos;s &lt;tt&gt;TestICUTokenizerCJK&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I plan to commit as soon as precommit passes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
